                <p class="font-inter text-2xl font-bold text-accent">Deloitte</p>
            </div>
            <h2 class="font-playfair text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold italic text-gray-800 leading-tight">Scaling Systems for a Global Team</h2>
            <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-start">
                <div class="md:col-span-1">
                     <div class="flex items-center">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="64" height="64" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-accent mr-4"><path d="M21.5 12c0-5.25-4.25-9.5-9.5-9.5S2.5 6.75 2.5 12s4.25 9.5 9.5 9.5"/><path d="M12 2.5v19"/><path d="M2.5 12h19"/></svg>
                        <div>
                           <p class="font-inter text-3xl font-bold text-accent">40+</p>
                           <p class="font-inter font-semibold text-gray-700">Team Members</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="md:col-span-2 border-t-2 md:border-t-0 md:border-l-2 border-gray-200 pt-6 md:pt-0 md:pl-8">
                    <h3 class="font-inter text-xl font-bold mb-3">The Problem</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
                        A system built for a small, co-located team in North America was failing to support a rapidly expanding global team. There were no shared standards, workflows, or taxonomies to handle different regions and time zones.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </header>

        <main>
            <section class="section-card p-8 md:p-12">
                <div class="max-w-3xl">
                    <h3 class="font-inter text-3xl font-bold mb-4">The Solution & My Work</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
                        I designed and implemented the foundational information systems needed to support the global expansion, enabling the team to work efficiently across multiple continents.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 1: Information Architecture -->
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-header">
                        <div class="step-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 3h6v6"/><path d="M10 14 21 3"/><path d="M14 10H3v11h11v-3"/><path d="M10 10v.01"/></svg></div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Global Information Architecture</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">I expanded the existing file structures to support global operations, implementing clear naming conventions that included regional identifiers to ensure assets were compliant and easily discoverable by local teams.</p>
                    <div class="artifact-container">
                        <p class="artifact-label">Artifact: Scaled File Naming Convention</p>
                         <div class="bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded-sm">
                            <h4 class="font-bold mb-2 text-center text-sm text-gray-400">GLOBAL STANDARD</h4>
                            <p class="code-snippet text-green-400">[YYYY-MM-DD]_[Region]_[Campaign]_[AssetType]_[v#]<br><br>ex: 2022-08-01_EMEA_SummerSale_Email_v2.psd<br>ex: 2022-07-25_APAC_ProductLaunch_Banner_v4.ai</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 2: Taxonomy -->
                 <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-header">
                        <div class="step-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21.44 11.05l-9.19 9.19a6 6 0 0 1-8.49-8.49l9.19-9.19a4 4 0 0 1 5.66 5.66l-9.2 9.19a2 2 0 0 1-2.83-2.83l8.49-8.48"/></svg></div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Globally-Aware Taxonomy</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">I established new metadata standards and classification systems that were globally consistent but allowed for regional flexibility. This ensured assets were searchable across the entire organization while still meeting local needs.</p>
                    <div class="artifact-container">
                        <p class="artifact-label">Artifact: Global Metadata Schema</p>
                        <div class="bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden"><table class="w-full text-sm"><thead class="bg-gray-800 text-white"><tr><th class="p-3 text-left font-semibold tracking-wider">Field Name</th><th class="p-3 text-left font-semibold tracking-wider">Field Type</th><th class="p-3 text-left font-semibold tracking-wider">Controlled Values / Description</th></tr></thead><tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200"><tr class="bg-white"><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Region</td><td class="p-3">Dropdown (Multi-select)</td><td class="p-3"><code class="text-xs">Global, NA, EMEA, APAC, LATAM</code></td></tr><tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Language</td><td class="p-3">Dropdown</td><td class="p-3"><code class="text-xs">EN-US, EN-GB, FR, ES, JP</code></td></tr><tr class="bg-white"><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Asset_Status</td><td class="p-3">Dropdown</td><td class="p-3">Global standard: <code class="text-xs">WIP, Review, Approved</code></td></tr><tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Legal_Compliance</td><td class="p-3">Checkbox</td><td class="p-3">Confirms asset meets local legal review requirements.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 3: Workflow -->
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-header">
                        <div class="step-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 6h3"/><path d="M5 2v4"/><path d="M19 6h3"/><path d="M17 2v4"/><path d="M21 14H3"/><path d="M3 10h18"/><path d="M5 14v4"/><path d="M17 14v4"/></svg></div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Asynchronous Workflow Adoption</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">A PM tool is useless if no one updates it. My work wasn't to invent a tool, but to architect and enforce the mandatory workflow that transformed the existing tool from a neglected ticket-tracker into a true "single source of truth" for the global team.</p>
                    <div class="artifact-container">
                        <p class="artifact-label">Artifact: Asynchronous Communication Workflow</p>
                        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                            <div>
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-center text-sm mb-2">THE PROCESS</h4>
                                <div class="flowchart">
                                    <div class="flowchart-step">Coordinator Creates Project Hub Task</div>
                                    <div class="flowchart-arrow"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></div>
                                    <div class="flowchart-step">Designer Posts Updates in Hub</div>
                                     <div class="flowchart-arrow"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></div>
                                    <div class="flowchart-step">Coordinator Reviews from Hub</div>
                                     <div class="flowchart-arrow"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg></div>
                                    <div class="flowchart-step">Final Asset Link Posted in Hub</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                               <h4 class="font-bold text-center text-sm mb-2">THE RESULT</h4>
                                <div class="project-hub">
                                    <div class="hub-header flex justify-between items-center">
                                        <div>
                                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">APAC Launch</h4>
                                            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">#PROJ-781</p>
                                        </div>
                                        <span class="hub-status status-review">In Review</span>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="hub-details text-xs">
                                        <div class="hub-detail-item"><span>Owner</span>A. George</div>
                                        <div class="hub-detail-item"><span>Region</span>APAC</div>
                                        <div class="hub-detail-item"><span>Designer</span>J. Smith (UK)</div>
                                        <div class="hub-detail-item"><span>Due Date</span>2022-07-28</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="hub-comments">
                                        <div class="hub-comment">
                                            <div class="hub-comment-avatar text-sm">JS</div>
                                            <div class="hub-comment-content">
                                                <p class="hub-comment-meta text-sm">J. Smith <span>(9:15 AM GMT)</span></p>
                                                <p class="mt-1 text-xs">@A. George - Drafts are linked in 'Assets' tab. Ready for your review.</p>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                           </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Step 4: Governance -->
                 <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-header">
                        <div class="step-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" x2="8" y1="13" y2="13"/><line x1="16" x2="8" y1="17" y2="17"/><line x1="10" x2="8" y1="9" y2="9"/></svg></div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Documented Global Standards</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">I collaborated with leadership to document and standardize these new global creative asset workflows, ensuring all teams had a central source of truth for how to work together across time zones.</p>
                     <div class="artifact-container">
                        <p class="artifact-label">Artifact: Global SOP Snippet</p>
                        <div class="sop-document"><div class="sop-header"><p class="sop-subtitle">GLOBAL STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURE</p><h4 class="sop-title">Cross-Team Asset Handoffs</h4></div><div class="sop-rule"><div class="sop-rule-number">01</div><div><h5 class="font-bold">Project Hub is the Source of Truth</h5><p class="text-sm mt-1">All status changes, feedback, and links to assets must be logged in the official project hub task. Communication outside the hub is unofficial.</p></div></div><div class="sop-rule"><div class="sop-rule-number">02</div><div><h5 class="font-bold">Tag for Region & Language</h5><p class="text-sm mt-1">All assets uploaded to the DAM must include correct `Region` and `Language` metadata tags.</p></div></div><div class="sop-rule"><div class="sop-rule-number">03</div><div><h5 class="font-bold">Allow 24hr Review Cycle</h5><p class="text-sm mt-1">Due to global time zones, all review deadlines must allow for a minimum 24-hour turnaround.</p></div></div></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                 <!-- Step 5: Payoff -->
                 <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-header">
                        <div class="step-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 6 9 17l-5-5"/></svg></div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">The Payoff</h3>
                    </div>
                     <div class="artifact-container mt-0">
                        <div class="payoff-card">
                            <p class="text">These systems provided the foundational structure that enabled a 40+ member global team to work efficiently across multiple time zones and regions.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
